abstract: Veteran socialist politician and author Michael D Higgins is on course to score a come-from-behind win in the race for president of the Irish Republic as his main rivals concede defeat before the final tallies are counted.
snippet: The veteran socialist politician and author was set to win as his two main rivals, including the perceived front-runner, Sean Gallagher, conceded the election.
lead_paragraph: The veteran socialist politician and author was set to win as his two main rivals, including the perceived front-runner, Sean Gallagher, conceded the election.

headline.main: Labour Party Leader Set to Win Ireland’s Presidential Election
headline.print_headline: Labour Party Leader Set to Win Ireland’s Presidential Election
headline.seo: Michael D. Higgins Set to Be Ireland’s New President
